  "title": "Administrative Assistant",
  "description": "<p>Administrative Assistants work to ensure that their client groups are supported appropriately through activities such as organizational logistics, expense administrative, travel coordination, and event logistics. Additionally, Assistants are responsible for building technological and foundational skills necessary to support decision making may involve cross-culture and high exposure clients, externally, and cross-functionally. <br /></p><p><strong>Job Role Summary</strong><br /><strong></strong></p><ul><li>Provide guided administrative support to client group.</li><li>May be functional based role that supports mid-level managers and events with limited exposure.</li><li>May support executing or overseeing key processes for a broader team rather than general, individualized support. </li><li>Develop foundational skills and knowledge to execute tasks and utilize technology.</li><li>Build skills by identifying resources. </li><li>Learn about the business through mentoring relationship and asking questions. </li></ul><p><strong>Job Role Responsibilities</strong><br /></p><ul><li>Manage expense reports, invoices, time writing and time keeping. </li><li>May coordinate scheduling of meetings for client groups.</li><li>Process personnel logistics activities including org charts and communication. </li><li>Manage office logistics.</li><li>Make travel arrangements as necessary. </li><li>May support a key process for a broader team or organization. </li></ul>",
